398%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fcrimea-nearly-500-000-left-without-power-after-storm-hits-black-sea-region-13017398%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Americans%20ditched%20big%20cities%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20Now%20many%20are%20regretting%20it.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20keychain%20containing%20%20a%20house%2C%20sad%20face%20and%20covid%20virus.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655d231f22cf74a5739b38d9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20dream%20of%20owning%20a%20home%20with%20a%20yard%20in%20the%20suburbs%20is%20turning%20out%20to%20be%20disappointing.%3Cp%3EChelsea%20Jia%20Feng%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESusan%2C%20a%2030-something%20artist%2C%20lived%20in%20New%20York%20City%20when%20the%20pandemic%20struck.%20Eager%20to%20flee%20the%20claustrophobia%20of%20a%20too-small%20apartment%2C%20she%20and%20her%20husband%20decamped%20upstate%20to%20stay%20with%20friends%20in%20an%20up-and-coming%20town%20in%20the%20Catskills%20(population%3A%201%2C000)%20where%20they%20could%20hike%20local%20trails%20and%20fish%20for%20trout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESusan%2C%20who%20asked%20that%20her%20real%20name%20not%20be%20used%20to%20avoid%20social%20repercussions%2C%20had%20lived%20in%20New%20York%20City%20for%20over%20a%20decade%2C%20but%20her%20husband%20had%20grown%20tired%20of%20the%20hustle%20and%20bustle%20of%20the%20city.%20The%20pair%20had%20talked%20about%20moving%20to%20a%20smaller%20town%20someday%20%E2%80%94%20the%20pandemic%20just%20shortened%20their%20timeline.%20Thanks%20to%20the%20influx%20of%20city%20folk%20desperate%20for%20personal%20space%2C%20rents%20in%20trendy%20upstate%20communities%20had%20become%20exorbitant%20overnight%2C%20so%20it%20made%20more%20financial%20sense%20to%20simply%20buy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20couple%20put%20in%20an%20offer%20on%20a%20home%20near