ties-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etry%20someplace%20new%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Maybe%2C%20like%20Susan%2C%20they%20had%20been%20planning%20a%20move%20for%20a%20while.%20Or%20maybe%20they%20just%20wanted%20to%20live%20somewhere%20more%20affordable.%20Regardless%20of%20the%20initial%20reasons%2C%20reality%20has%20clearly%20smacked%20many%20of%20these%20people%20in%20the%20face.%20For%20many%20millennial%20homebuyers%20in%20particular%2C%20they%20relocated%20from%20cities%20to%20the%20suburbs%20and%20semirural%20areas%20where%20homes%20were%20cheaper%20but%20further%20away%20from%20the%20social%20and%20professional%20networks%20they'd%20cultivated%20throughout%20their%20young%20adulthoods.%20Some%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-workers-moved-to-austin-regrets-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estruggled%20to%20assimilate%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20their%20new%20communities.%20Many%20feel%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fincredibly-lonely-high-paying-tech-job-seattle-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecut%20off%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20their%20identities%2C%20hobbies%2C%20and%20the%20friends%20they%20left%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20thread%20running%20through%20many%20of%20these%20stories%20is%20the%20pursuit%20of%20a%20dream%20that%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20nothing%20like%20what%20was%20expected%20%E2%80%94%20the%20dream%20of%20a%20three-bedroom%20house%20with%20a%20covered%20front%20porch%20and%20enough%20yard%20for%20a%20few%20kids%20and%20a%20dog%20to%20play%20safely%2C%20close%20to%20nature%20and%20far%20from%20city%20noise.%20But%20what%20many%20Americans%20are%20coming%20to%20realize%20is%20that%20there%20are%20no%20good%20options.%20As%20everything%20gets%20more%20expensive%20and%20it%20gets%20harder%20to%20make%20new%20friends%2C%20deciding%20where%20to%20live%20is%20a%20multilayered%20compromise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMillennials%20are%20bucking%20old%20trends%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20usually%20went%20like%20this%3A%20Young%20people%20would%20move%20to%20the%20city%20in%20their%20early%2020s%20to%20start%20their%20careers%20and%20meet%20people.%20Then%2C%20as%20they%20hit%20their%20mid-20s%20to%20early%2030s%2C%20they%20would%20get%20married%2C%20settle%20down%20in%20the%20suburbs%2C%20and%20start%20having%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20the%20oldest%20millennials%20disrupted%20that%20trend.%20Riordan%20Frost%2C%20a%20senior%20research%20analyst%20at%20Harvard's%20Joint%20Center%20for%20Housing%20Studies%2C%20said%20fewer%20people%20in%20their%2030s%20(specifically%2C%20those%20born%20between%201977%20and%201986)%20moved%20to%20the%20suburbs%20between%202011%20and%202021%20than%20people%20of%20a%20similar%20age%20did%20in%20previous%20decades.%20Millennials%20are%20consistently%20more%20likely%20than%20their%20predecessors%20to%20reside%20in%20cities%2C%20a%20trend%20that%20some%20demographers%20attribute%20to%20millennials'%20%26quot%3Bdelay%26quot%3B%20in%20achieving%20major%20milestones%20like%20getting%20married%2C%20having%20kids%2C%20and%20buying%20their%20first%20home.%20Coming%20of%20age%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%202008%20recession%20was%20a%20challenge%2C%20but%20when%20millennials%20%26quot%3Bcatch%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20theory%20goes%2C%20they'll%20follow%20suit%20and%20pack%20up%20to%20the%20land%20of%20McMansions%20and%20cul-de-sacs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20exactly%20what%20some%20millennials%20did%20when%20the%20pandemic%20hit.%20And%20when%20they%20fled%20cities%20for%20the%20suburbs%2C%20they%20went%20all%20out.%20Far%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20kind%20of%20thought%20that%20they%20would%20be%20going%20to%20more%20urbanized%20suburban%20areas%2C%20places%20that%20are%20technically%20suburban%20but%20more%20urban%20in%20character%2C%26quot%3B%20Frost%2C%20who%20published%20a%20research%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jchs.harvard.edu%2Fresearch-areas%2Fresearch-briefs%2Fdid-more-people-move-during-pandemic%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebrief%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20subject%20in%20March%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20we%20found%20that%20they%20were%20primarily%20going%20out%20to%20these%20farther-flung%2C%20more%20peripheral%20suburban%20areas.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeading%20the%20charge%20were%20older%20millennial%20homebuyers.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nar.realtor%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2F2021-home-buyers-and-sellers-generational-trends-03-16-2021.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EData%20from%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Realtors%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20between%202020%20and%202021%2C%2054%25%20of%20homebuyers%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2031%20and%2040%20bought%20homes%20in%20a%20suburb%20or%20subdivision%2C%20while%2031%25%20opted%20to%20buy%20in%20a%20small%20town%20or%20rural%20area.%20The%20overwhelming%20majority%20of%20the%20properties%20they%20purchased%20%E2%80%94%2088%25%20%E2%80%94%20were%20single-family%2C%20detached%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20people%20who%20left%20cities%20with%20fewer%20large%20apartments%20and%20houses%20tended%20to%20move%20to%20the%20outer%20limits%20of%20their%20metro%20areas%2C%20Frost%20and%20his%20colleagues%20found.%20Though%20their%20analysis%20did%20not%20explicitly%20look%20at%20the%20reasons%20behind%20the%20trend%2C%20Frost%20hypothesizes%20that%20cost%20is%20a%20significant%20factor.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20people%20are%20buying%20houses%2C%20they're%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20going%20farther%20out%20because%20they're%20trying%20to%20get%20something%20they%20can%20afford%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20big-city%20rents%20go%20up%2C%20that%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20significant%20motivation%20behind%20many%20pandemic%20moves%3A%20People%20hunting%20for%20more%20space%20at%20a%20price%20they%20can%20afford.%20But%20as%20the%20moving%20frenzy%20has%20subsided%20and%20returned%20to%20pre-pandemic%20levels%2C%20many%20pandemic%20movers%20%E2%80%94%20millennials%20and%20other%20generations%20alike%20%E2%80%94%20are%20getting%20a%20more%20clear-eyed%20view%20of%20what%20they%20signed%20up%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20good%20options%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlex%20Gatien%2C%20a%2038-year-old%20city%20planner%2C%20left%20Toronto%20in%20May%202021%20for%20a%20much%20smaller%20Canadian%20city%20270%20miles%20east%2C%20perched%20on%20the%20St.%20Lawrence%20River%20and%20within%20minutes%20of%20the%20US%20border.%20Though%20he%20moved%20for%20a%20job%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20in%20Toronto%20had%20become%20untenable.%20Over%20the%20years%2C%20he's%20watched%20as%20more%20and%20more%20of%20his%20friends%20have%20been%20priced%20out%20of%20the%20city%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Famericas%2Fpandemic-exodus-canadian-families-cities-could-fuel-wage-inflation-2022-02-13%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20trend%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20became%20especially%20pronounced%20early%20in%20the%20pandemic.%20For%20less%20than%20the%20cost%20of%20a%20studio%20condo%20in%20Toronto%2C%20Gatien%20and%20his%20partner%20purchased%20a%20four-bedroom%20Victorian%20with%20a%20large%20yard%20in%20their%20new%20city's%20historic%20downtown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20paper%2C%20they're%20living%20the%20homeownership%20dream.%20In%20reality%2C%20the%20suburbanized%20small-city%20lifestyle%20feels%20a%20lot%20more%20like%20a%20trade-off.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20live%20in%20a%20much%20more%20private%20realm%2C%26quot%3B%20Gatien%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BEveryone%20drives%20everywhere%2C%20which%20means%20you%20don't%20really%20run%20into%20people.%20They%20don't%20really%20use%20public%20spaces%20like%20parks%20unless%20they%20don't%20have%20their%20own%20outdoor%20space%2C%20which%20everyone%20does%20unless%20they're%20poor.%26quot%3B%20Though%20he%20knew%20what%20he%20was%20signing%20up%20for%20and%20he%20appreciates%20the%20low%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20Gatien%20laments%20what%20he%20gave%20up%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanada-housing-crisis-bubble-imploding-real-estate-prices-rent-decline-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECanada%20is%20struggling%20with%20a%20similar%20housing%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20US%2C%20and%20the%20dilemma%20Gatien%20faced%20is%20the%20same%20that%20more%20Americans%20are%20reckoning%20with.%20Remote%20work%20opened%20up%20a%20Pandora's%20box%20of%20places%20to%20call%20home.%20And%20all%20sorts%20of%20factors%2C%20from%20weather%20to%20proximity%20to%20family%20(some%20of%20them%20contradictory)%2C%20influence%20people's%20decisions%20about%20where%20to%20settle%20down.%20But%20even%20when%20you%20carefully%20weigh%20your%20options%2C%20do%20your%20research%2C%20and%20make%20a%20thoughtful%20decision%2C%20the%20reality%20of%20a%20barren%20housing%20market%20can%20be%20disappointing.%20For%20many%2C%20the%20only%20real%20options%20are%20rife%20with%20compromise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20it's%20partly%20a%20problem%20of%20our%20own%20making.%20In%20a%20perverse%20twist%20of%20fate%2C%20the%20American%20ideal%20of%20having%20a%20single-family%20house%20of%20your%20own%20%E2%80%94%20complete%20with%20a%20large%2C%20private%20lot%20%E2%80%94%20has%20made%20it%20harder%20for%20people%20to%20purchase%3Cem%3E%20any%3C%2Fem%3E%20kind%20of%20home%2C%20which%20in%20turn%2C%20has%20led%20more%20people%20to%20leave%20big%20cities%20for%20more%20affordable%20locales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20Susan%2C%20the%20New%20York%20artist.%20Her%20move%20upstate%20was%20motivated%20both%20by%20circumstance%20and%20economic%20pragmatism%2C%20and%20predicated%20on%20giving%20up%20big%20city%20life%20for%20the%20slower%20pace%20of%20the%20country.%20It%20was%20also%20a%20favor%20to%20her%20husband%2C%20who%20never%20felt%20at%20peace%20in%20the%20bustle%20of%20the%20big%20city.%20But%20once%20the%20deal%20was%20done%20and%20she%20got%20over%20the%20initial%20shock%2C%20she%20warmed%20up%20to%20what%20she%20describes%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20fantasy%26quot%3B%20of%20having%20a%20house%20with%20a%20backyard%20that%20is%20close%20to%20nature%2C%20especially%20if%20and%20when%20she%20and%20her%20husband%20decide%20to%20start%20a%20family.%20%26quot%3BIt%20wasn't%20one%20that%20either%20of%20us%20were%20pursuing%20wholeheartedly%2C%20but%20once%20we%20made%20the%20move%2C%20we%20liked%20the%20potential%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20about%20being%20able%20to%20start%20a%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20ideal%20is%20more%20deeply%20entrenched%20in%20American%20culture%20%E2%80%94%20and%20its%20housing%20policies%20%E2%80%94%20than%20you%20might%20think.%20%26quot%3BIn%20American%20history%2C%20the%20desire%20for%20an%20independently%20owned%20house%20with%20at%20least%20an%20excuse%20for%20a%20yard%20goes%20way%20back%2C%20at%20least%20to%20the%20late%201700s%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Alexander%20von%20Hoffman%2C%20an%20urban%20planner%20and%20historian%20also%20with%20Harvard's%20Joint%20Center%20for%20Housing%20Studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20cities%20grew%20and%20their%20economies%20expanded%2C%20densely%20packed%20row%20housing%20and%20multiunit%20developments%20sprung%20up%20to%20accommodate%20the%20people%20who%20worked%20in%20the%20ports%2C%20railways%2C%20and%20industrial%20facilities%20that%20those%20cities%20were%20built%20around.%20%26quot%3BAs%20early%20as%20the%20early%201800s%2C%20the%20housing%20market%20fragmented%20by%20the%20ability%20to%20pay%2C%26quot%3B%20von%20Hoffman%20continued.%20%26quot%3BEven%20at%20the%20low%20end%20of%20the%20market%2C%20where%20possible%2C%20there%20has%20always%20been%20a%20propensity%20to%20own%20a%20house%2C%20preferably%20detached%2C%20with%20a%20yard.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20stubborn%20adherence%20to%20an%20ideal%20of%20single-family%20property%20ownership%20in%20place%20of%20denser%20housing%20gave%20rise%20to%20the%20restrictive%20residential-zoning%20laws%20and%20caps%20on%20new%20affordable-housing%20builds%20that%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faffordable-housing-crisis-us-west-coast-cause-explained-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edriving%20our%20current%20housing%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20would%20call%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyimbys-winning-lower-house-prices-rents-build-more-homes-neighborhoods-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENIMBYism%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Sandro%20Galea%2C%20an%20epidemiologist%20and%20the%20dean%20of%20the%20Boston%20University%20School%20of%20Public%20Health%2C%20uses%20the%20phrase%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.psychologytoday.com%2Fus%2Fblog%2Ftalking-about-health%2F202109%2Fseeing-past-the-white-picket-fence%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esuburban%20impulses%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20perfectly%20reasonable%20for%20people%20to%20want%20to%20have%20a%20stable%2C%20comfortable%2C%20safe%20living%20environment%2C%20but%20so%20does%20everybody%20else%2C%20and%20what%20we%20want%20for%20ourselves%20should%20not%20come%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20what%20we%20should%20want%20collectively%2C%26quot%3B%20Galea%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20byproduct%20of%20both%20rigid%20zoning%20policies%20and%20suburban%20norms%20is%20the%20decades-long%20decline%20of%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floneliness-epidemic-decline-in-third-places-friends-parks-community-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethird%20spaces%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20such%20as%20coffee%20shops%20and%20public%20libraries%2C%20where%20people%20can%20hang%20out%20and%20meet%20others.%20Without%20spaces%20like%20these%20to%20gather%2C%20it%20can%20be%20especially%20difficult%20for%20recent%20transplants%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fhow-to-make-friends-as-adult-moving-cities-nyc-la-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emake%20friends%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20their%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20those%20who%20stay%20in%20the%20cities%20and%20watch%20their%20rent%20skyrocket%20and%20those%20who%20choose%20to%20go%20someplace%20more%20affordable%20are%20feeling%20the%20weight%20of%20the%20same%20dilemma.%20Do%20you%20stay%20in%20the%20small%2C%20expensive%20apartment%20that%20is%20close%20to%20friends%3F%20Or%20do%20you%20give%20that%20up%20for%20the%20often-lonely%20dream%20of%20a%20single-family%20home%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Susan%2C%20the%20benefits%20of%20country%20life%20never%20quite%20made%20up%20for%20the%20costs.%20A%20few%20months%20ago%2C%20she%20and%20her%20husband%20found%20a%20renter%20for%20their%20house%20and%20returned%20to%20the%20city.%20She%20said%20that%20subletting%20an%20apartment%20in%20the%20city%20that%20she%20could%20imagine%20herself%20living%20in%20a%20decade%20ago%20sometimes%20feels%20like%20a%20step%20backward.%20And%20she's%20not%20sure%20how%20long%20they'll%20stay%20before%20going%20back%20upstate.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20she%20feels%20like%20herself%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fkelli-maria-korducki%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EKelli%20Mar%C3%ADa%20Korducki%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20journalist%20whose%20work%20focuses%20on%20work%2C%20tech%2C%20and%20culture.%20She's%20based%20in%20New%20York%20City.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericans-regretting-moves-from-city-to-suburbs-housing-crisis-millennials-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701081721000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655d23734ca513d8242d506e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fameri