.com%2F655e77be22cf74a5739bd872%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224550%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBonnie%20Dilber%20says%20there%20are%20three%20interview%20questions%20you%20should%20be%20answering%20with%20care.%3Cp%3ESvetaZi%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EBonnie%20Dilber%20is%20a%20recruiting%20manager%20with%20nine%20years%20of%20experience.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBecause%20of%20the%20ultra-competitive%20job%20market%2C%20the%20smallest%20things%20can%20prevent%20you%20from%20getting%20hired.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECandidates%20should%20think%20about%20how%20to%20answer%20these%20simple%20questions%20carefully.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Bonnie%20Dilber%2C%20a%20recruiting%20manager%20at%20Zapier%2C%20a%20remote-first%20SaaS%20company%20in%20the%20automation%20industry.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20challenging%20time%20for%20job%20seekers%20%E2%80%94%20the%20market%20is%20highly%20competitive%2C%20with%20hundreds%20of%20applicants%20for%20every%20single%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20recruiting%20manager%20with%20nine%20years%20of%20experience%2C%20I%20understand%20that%20companies%20want%20to%20hire%20top%20talent%20that%20will%20grow%20with%20them%20over%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20to%20present%20yourself%20in%20this%20way%2C%20here%20are%20three%20interview%20questions%20you%20should%20be%20answering%20with%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuestion%20No.%201%3A%20Why%20did%20you%20leave%20your%20last%20job%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20red%20flag%20answer%20is%20any%20response%20that%20involves%20being%20overly%20negative%20or%20bashing%20a%20former%20employer.%20It%20makes%20the%20interviewing%20company%20concerned%20about%20whether%20the%20issues%20were%20with%20you%20or%20the%20workplace.%20They%20may%20also%20worry%20that%20you%20could%20speak%20negatively%20about%20them%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20red%20flag%20answer%20will%20look%20like%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20manager%20was%20micromanaging%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20leadership%20of%20the%20company%20has%20no%20idea%20what%20they're%20doing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20more%20positive%20or%20%26quot%3Bgreen%20flag%26quot%3B%20response%20would%20be%20to%20focus%20on%20what%20the%20candidate%20is%20seeking%20in%20their%20next%20role%20and%20what%20excites%20them.%20If%20it's%20necessary%20to%20mention%20something%20less%20positive%20about%20a%20former%20company%2C%20keep%20it%20brief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20green%20flag%20answer%20will%20look%20like%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThings%20were%20going%20great%2C%20but%20I%20wanted%20to%20take%20on%20more%20challenges.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20left%20because%20I%20think%20it%20wasn't%20the%20best%20culture%20fit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20I'm%20looking%20for%20in%20this%20role%20wasn't%20as%20interesting%20as%20I%20thought%20it%20would%20be.%20I'd%20like%20to%20find%20something%20that%20better%20aligns%20with%20my%20interest.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuestion%20No.%202%3A%20Why%20do%20you%20want%20the%20job%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20exclusively%20focused%20on%20what%20you're%20going%20to%20get%20out%20of%20the%20company%2C%20like%2C%20compensation%20benefits%2C%20and%20remote%20work%20flexibility%2C%20the%20company%20may%20think%20that%20you%20don't%20care%20enough%20about%20that%20job%20or%20the%20company%20%E2%80%94%20you're%20making%20them%20think%20that%20you're%20going%20for%20what%20is%20convenient%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20being%20said%2C%20realistically%2C%20a%20remote%20company%20knows%20that%20you're%20excited%20because%20the%20job%20pays%20well%20and%20it's%20flexible.%20However%2C%20what%20they're%20looking%20for%20are%20candidates%20who%20show%20up%20better%20on%20a%20question%20and%20go%20beyond%20talking%20about%20compensation%20and%20benefits.%20They%20want%20someone%20who%20has%20done%20their%20research%2C%20understands%20what%20the%20company%20does%2C%20and%20shows%20enthusiasm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20red%20flag%20answer%20will%20look%20like%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20looking%20for%20a%20remote%20job%20so%20I%20can%20be%20home%20with%20my%20kids.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20want%20the%20job%20because%20it%20pays%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20green%20flag%20answer%20here%20is%20one%20that%20focuses%20on%20what%20excites%20you%20about%20the%20job%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20excited%20about%20the%20potential%20impact%20of%20the%20products%20the%20company%20is%20creating%2C%20and%20I%20really%20want%20to%20be%20a%20part%20of%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuestion%20No.%203%3A%20Where%20do%20you%20see%20yourself%20in%20the%20future%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20expensive%20to%20hire%20and%20train%20someone%20%E2%80%94%20companies%20hope%20to%20hire%20someone%20who%20will%20stay%20long-term.%20It%20is%20important%20to%20indicate%20your%20hopes%20to%20do%20well%20in%20the%20role%20and%20grow%20with%20the%20company%20long-term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20it's%20especially%20concerning%20for%20companies%20if%20someone%20applies%20for%20a%20job%20that%20they're%20overqualified%20for%20%E2%80%94%20they%20might%20think%20the%20candidate%20will%20leave%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELet's%20say%2C%20someone%20has%20been%20in%20management%20for%20the%20past%20five%20years%20and%20now%20is%20applying%20for%20an%20individual%20contributor%20role.%20If%20the%20person%20says%20something%20like%20%26quot%3BI%20haven't%20been%20able%20to%20get%20interviews%20for%20management%20ro