virus%2C%20and%20respiratory%20syncytial%20virus%2C%20following%20a%20decline%20in%20mycoplasma-caused%20pneumonia%20in%20children.%20The%20spread%20of%20these%20pathogens%20may%20lead%20to%20a%20major%20outbreak%20between%20now%20and%20next%20spring.%20Health%20experts%20believe%20that%20the%20culprit%20is%20likely%20an%20existing%20germ%20rather%20than%20a%20new%20pathogen.%20Mycoplasma%2C%20a%20common%20pathogen%20causing%20pneumonia%20in%20children%2C%20has%20a%20high%20local%20resistance%20to%20antibiotics%20in%20China.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Bloomberg%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20the%20List%20of%20Palestinians%20Released%20in%20the%20Exchange%20Says%20About%20Israel%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27093258%2FF_uue79W8AAJQNu.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael%20and%20Hamas%20are%20acting%20on%20an%20agreement%20to%20pause%20hostilities%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20nearly%20seven%20weeks%20into%20the%20war.%20The%20deal%20included%20a%20four-day%20ceasefire%20and%20an%20exchange%20of%2050%20Israeli%20hostages%20for%20150%20Palestinian%20%E2%80%9Csecurity%20prisoners%2C%E2%80%9D%20with%20the%20possibility%20of%20further%20exchanges%20thereafter.%20These%20are%20terms%20that%20Hamas%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Fnov%2F09%2Fnetanyahu-rejected-ceasefire-for-hostages-deal-in-gaza-sources-say%5C%22%3Ereportedly%20offered%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0Israel%20weeks%20ago%20in%20the%20early%20phases%20of%20the%20war%2C%20but%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20preferred%20to%20wage%20an%20all-out%20assault%20on%20the%20besieged%20Strip%2C%20killing%20more%20than%2014%2C000%20Palestinians%2C%20before%20considering%20a%20deal%20%E2%80%94%20even%20at%20the%20detriment%20of%20the%20safety%20and%20wellbeing%20of%20the%20Israeli%20hostages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael%20has%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.il%2Fhe%2FDepartments%2FDynamicCollectors%2Fis-db%3Fskip%3D0%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20names%20of%20300%20Palestinian%20prisoners%20that%20it%20is%20considering%20releasing%20as%20part%20of%20the%20deal%20or%20upon%20the%20freeing%20of%20more%20Israeli%20hostages%2C%20in%20order%20to%20allow%20for%20legal%20appeals%20in%20Israeli%20courts%20against%20the%20release%20of%20specific%20individuals.%20All%20of%20the%20hostages%20and%20prisoners%20to%20be%20exchanged%20at%20this%20stage%20are%20women%20and%20minors.%20Still%2C%20many%20among%20the%20Israeli%20right%2C%20and%20perhaps%20the%20wider%20public%2C%20believe%20that%20the%20government%20is%20making%20a%20significant%20concession%20by%20releasing%20dangerous%20%E2%80%9Cterrorists%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20the%20few%20hostages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReading%20through%20the%20list%20of%20Palestinian%20prisoners%20slated%20for%20release%2C%20the%20first%20thing%20that%20strikes%20you%20is%20their%20ages.%20The%20vast%20majority%20of%20them%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.timesofisrael.com%2Fliveblog_entry%2Fisrael-publishes-details-of-palestinian-prisoners-to-be-released-as-part-of-hostage-deal%2F%5C%22%3E287%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20are%20aged%2018%20or%20under%2C%20including%20five%20as%20young%20as%2014%2C%20which%20begs%20the%20question%3A%20how%20does%20a%2014-year-old%20boy%20become%20a%20%E2%80%9Csecurity%20prisoner%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20names%20on%20the%20list%20include%20alleged%20members%20of%20Palestinian%20political%20factions%20like%20Hamas%2C%20Fatah%2C%20Islamic%20Jihad%2C%20and%20the%20Popular%20Front%20for%20the%20Liberation%20of%20Palestine%20(PFLP)%2C%20as%20well%20as%20many%20who%20are%20not%20affiliated%20with%20any%20group.%20None%20were%20convicted%20of%20murder.%20Some%20were%20convicted%20of%20attempted%20murder%2C%20while%20the%20majority%20were%20charged%20with%20less%20significant%20offences%2C%20including%20a%20large%20number%20who%20were%20arrested%20for%20throwing%20stones.%20One%20of%20them%2C%20a%2017-year-old%2C%20has%20been%20behind%20bars%20for%20two%20years%20for%20throwing%20stones%20at%20an%20Israeli%20police%20vehicle%20in%20Jerusalem%20%E2%80%94%20the%20same%20city%20where%20Jewish%20settlers%20can%20carry%20out%20riots%20against%20Palestinians%20that%20rarely%20end%20in%20investigations%2C%20let%20alone%20arrests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20all%2C%20the%20list%20is%20a%20dizzying%20testament%20to%20just%20how%20central%20detention%20and%20imprisonment%20are%20to%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20occupation%20and%20control%20over%20Palestinians.%20According%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhamoked.org.il%2Fprisoners-charts.php%5C%22%3Edata%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0from%20the%20Israeli%20human%20rights%20group%20HaMoked%2C%20as%20of%20November%202023%2C%20Israel%20holds%206%2C809%20%E2%80%9Csecurity%20prisoners.%E2%80%9D%20Of%20these%2C%202%2C313%20are%20serving%20a%20prison%20sentence%3B%202%2C321%20have%20not%20yet%20been%20convicted%20in%20court%3B%202%2C070%20are%20being%20held%20under%20administrative%20detention%20(indefinitely%20imprisoned%20without%20trial%20or%20due%20process)%3B%20and%20105%20are%20%E2%80%9Cillegal%20combatants%E2%80%9D%20who%20were%20arrested%20during%20Hamas%E2%80%99%20October%207%20attacks%20in%20southern%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlmost%20all%20of%20the%20300%20Palestinians%20considered%20for%20release%20are%20relatively%20new%20prisoners%2C%20arrested%20in%20the%20last%20year%20or%20two.%20The%20exceptions%20are%2010%20women%20from%20Jerusalem%20and%20the%20West%20Bank%20who%20have%20been%20imprisoned%20since%202015-17%2C%20most%20of%20them%20on%20charges%20of%20attempting%20or%20committing%20stabbing%20attacks%20against%20Israeli%20security%20forces%20%E2%80%94%20some%20of%20which%20ended%20without%20any%20harm%2C%20while%20others%20caused%20minor%20to%20moderate%20injuries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20this%2C%20it%20should%20be%20recalled%2C%20is%20overseen%20by%20the%20same%20judicial%20system%20that%2C%20among%20countless%20other%20examples%2C%20decided%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.972mag.com%2Fsettler-stabbed-killed-ali-harb%2F%5C%22%3Eclose%20the%20case%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0against%20an%20Israeli%20settler%20who%20stabbed%20a%20young%20Palestinian%20to%20death%20in%20May%202022%20because%20%E2%80%9Cit%20was%20not%20possible%20to%20rule%20out%20%5Bthe%20suspect%E2%80%99s%5D%20version%20that%20he%20acted%20in%20self-defense.%E2%80%9D%20It%20is%20the%20same%20system%20that%2C%20in%20July%20of%20this%20year%2C%20acquitted%20an%20Israeli%20police%20officer%20who%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.972mag.com%2Fiyad-al-hallaq-police-court-acquittal%2F%5C%22%3Eshot%20dead%20Iyad%20al-Hallaq%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20autistic%20Palestinian%20man%2C%20despite%20clear%20testimonies%20and%20video%20evidence%20proving%20he%20was%20unarmed%20and%20made%20no%20threat%20of%20any%20kind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20Palestinian%20%E2%80%9Csecurity%20prisoners%E2%80%9D%20are%20judged%20in%20a%20separate%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.972mag.com%2Ftopic%2Fmilitary-courts%2F%5C%22%3Emilitary%20court%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20boasts%20a%20conviction%20rate%20of%20between%2095%20to%2099%20percent.%C2%A0Lenience%2C%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20the%20Israeli%20apartheid%20regime%2C%20is%20a%20right%20reserved%20for%20Jews%20only.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Jews%20who%20riot%2C%20attack%2C%20and%20even%20kill%20Palestinians%20are%20immune%20from%20prosecution%2C%20the%20prisoners%20list%20reminds%20us%20that%20Palestinians%20can%20be%20arrested%20wholesale%20based%20solely%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Cintention%E2%80%9D%20to%20carry%20out%20a%20violent%20act.%20One%20of%20those%20on%20the%20list%2C%20a%2045-year-old%20woman%20from%20Jerusalem%2C%20has%20been%20in%20prison%20for%20more%20than%20two%20years%20because%20%E2%80%9Cshe%20was%20caught%20in%20the%20Old%20City%20with%20a%20knife%20in%20her%20hand%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Csaid%20that%20she%20intended%20to%20carry%20out%20an%20attack.%E2%80%9D%20Meanwhile%2C%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20Kahanist%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.972mag.com%2Fben-gvir-ministry-kahane%2F%5C%22%3Enational%20security%20minister%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20urging%20Jews%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.972mag.com%2Fguns-israel-america-supremacy%2F%5C%22%3Earm%20themselves%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0while%20handing%20out%20weapons%20like%20candy%2C%20and%20many%20right-wing%20Israelis%20are%20writing%20countless%20messages%2C%20in%20public%20and%20private%2C%20gleefully%20announcing%20their%20intention%20to%20%E2%80%9Cmurder%20as%20many%20Arabs%20as%20possible.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESometimes%20%E2%80%9Cintent%E2%80%9D%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20even%20appear%20on%20the%20list%20of%20charges.%20An%2018-year-old%20from%20Jerusalem%20was%20%E2%80%9Carrested%20along%20with%20others%20because%20he%20cried%20out%20%E2%80%98Allahu%20Akbar.%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%20An%2018-year-old%20woman%20from%20the%20West%20Bank%20has%20been%20imprisoned%20for%20months%20for%20%E2%80%9Cincitement%20on%20Instagram.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20Israeli%20public%20in%20contrast%2C%20explicit%20calls%20for%20genocide%20are%20considered%20a%20legitimate%20way%20to%20raise%20the%20national%20morale%2C%20while%20Palestinians%20with%20Israeli%20citizenship%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.haaretz.co.il%2Fnews%2Flaw%2F2023-10-30%2Fty-article%2F.premium%2F0000018b-7c89-d4a8-a3cf-fca967310000%5C%22%3Emay%20be%20arrested%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20posting%20something%20as%20simple%20as%20a%20photo%20of%20shakshuka%20next%20to%20the%20Palestinian%20flag.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20indictments%20listed%2C%20only%20a%20few%20are%20related%20to%20the%20use%20of%20weapons%20and%20opening%20fire%20on%20Israeli%20forces%20(and%20even%20in%20these%20cases%2C%20there%20were%20no%20fatalities).%20The%20vast%20majority%20of%20incidents%20involve%20throwing%20stones%20or%20Molotov%20cocktails%2C%20shooting%20fireworks%2C%20and%20causing%20%E2%80%9Cpublic%20disorder.%E2%80%9D%20Was%20it%20worth%20letting%20Israeli%20hostages%2C%20women%2C%20and%20children%2C%20languish%20in%20Gaza%20for%20a%20few%20more%20weeks%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20continuing%20to%20imprison%20a%20young%20man%20who%20dared%20to%20cry%20%E2%80%9CGod%20is%20great%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20this%20list%20is%20composed%20of%20%E2%80%9Csoft%E2%80%9D%20prisoners%2C%20who%20won%E2%80%99t%20arouse%20as%20much%20public%20opposition%2C%20while%20Palestinian%20prisoners%20who%20have%20been%20charged%20with%20far%20more%20severe%20and%20deadly%20crimes%20remain%20in%20Israeli%20jails.%20But%20the%20300%20names%20that%20Israel%20was%20able%20to%20put%20together%20%E2%80%94%20almost%20all%20of%20them%20young%2C%20arrested%20in%20the%20last%20two%20years%2C%20and%20doing%20time%20for%20some%20form%20of%20popular%20resistance%20%E2%80%94%20should%20lead%20to%20some%20reflection%20among%20Israelis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%2C%20after%20all%2C%20a%20clear%20connection%20between%20the%20heavy-handed%20suppression%20of%20any%20expression%20of%20Palestinian%20opposition%2C%20and%20the%20strengthening%20of%20armed%20groups%20that%20see%20violence%20as%20the%20only%20way%20to%20seriously%20challenge%20their%20occupiers.%20But%20this%20would%20require%20the%20Israeli%20public%20to%20finally%20grasp%20the%20basic%20fact%20that%20as%20long%20as%20oppression%20continues%2C%20resistance%20will%20inevitably%20continue%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThis%20article%20first%20appeared%20on%20%2B972.%20Read%20the%20original%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.972mag.com%2Fpalestinian-prisoners-israeli-hostages-exchange%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20version%20of%20this%20article%20first%20appeared%20in%20Hebrew%20on%20%3C%2Fi%3ELocal%20Call%3Ci%3E.%20Read%20it%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mekomit.co.il%2F%25d7%2590%25d7%2599%25d7%259a-%25d7%2599%25d7%259c%25d7%2593-%25d7%2591%25d7%259f-14-%25d7%2594%25d7%2595%25d7%25a4%25d7%259a-%25d7%259c%25d7%2590%25d7%25a1%25d7%2599%25d7%25a8-%25d7%2591%25d7%2599%25d7%2598%25d7%2597%25d7%2595%25d7%25a0%25d7%2599-%25d7%2591%25d7%25a7%25d7%259c%25d7%2595%25d7%25aa-%25d7%25a8%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3Ehere%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIt%20has%20been%20edited%20slightly%20for%20tense.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EOrly%20Noy%20is%20an%20editor%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3ELocal%20Call%3Cem%3E%2C%20a%20political%20activist%2C%20and%20a%20translator%20of%20Farsi%20poetry%20and%20prose.%20She%20is%20the%20chair%20of%20B%E2%80%99Tselem%E2%80%99s%20executive%20board%20and%20an%20activist%20with%20the%20Balad%20political%20party.%20Her%20writing%20deals%20with%20the%20lines%20that%20intersect%20and%20define%20her%20identity%20as%20Mizrahi%2C%20a%20female%20leftist%2C%20a%20woman%2C%20a%20temporary%20migrant%20living%20inside%20a%20perpetual%20immigrant%2C%20and%20the%20constant%20dialogue%20between%20them.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701058218000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27093258%2FF_uue79W8AAJQNu.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fwhat-the-list-of-palestinians-released-in-the-exchange-says-about-israel%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20list%20of%20Palestinians%20slated%20to%20be%20exchanged%20for%20Israelis%20is%20a%20dizzying%20testament%20to%20just%20how%20central%20detention%20and%20imprisonment%20are%20to%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20occupation%20and%20control%20over%20Palestinians.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fwhat-the-list-of-palestinians-released-in-the-exchange-says-about-israel%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Irish%20Writer%20Paul%20Lynch%20Wins%20Booker%20Prize%20for%20%E2%80%98Prophet%20Song%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27090716%2FUntitled-design-6-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIrish%20writer%20Paul%20Lynch%20has%20won%20the%20prestigious%20Booker%20Prize%20for%20fiction%20for%20his%20fifth%20novel%2C%20%3Cem%3EProphet%20Song.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20dystopian%20novel%20is%20about%20a%20woman%E2%80%99s%20struggle%20to%20protect%20her%20family%20as%20Ireland%20collapses%20into%20totalitarianism%20in%20the%20near%20future.%20A%20civil%20war%20in%20Ireland%20then%20forces%20families%20to%20flee%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPaul%20Lynch%2C%2046%2C%20spent%20four%20years%20writing%20the%20book%20and%20was%20brought%20to%20the%20thought%20by%20the%20long%20years%20of%20the%20civil%20war%20in%20Syria%20and%20the%20%E2%80%9CWest%E2%80%99s%20indifference.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20was%20trying%20to%20see%20into%20the%20modern%20chaos%2C%E2%80%9D%20Lynch%20told%20the%20Booker%20website.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20unrest%20in%20Western%20democracies.%20The%20problem%20of%20Syria%20%E2%80%94%20the%20implosion%20of%20an%20entire%20nation%2C%20the%20scale%20of%20its%20refugee%20crisis%20and%20the%20West%E2%80%99s%20indifference.%20%E2%80%A6%20I%20wanted%20to%20deepen%20the%20reader%E2%80%99s%20immersion%20to%20such%20a%20degree%20that%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20book%2C%20they%20would%20not%20just%20know%2C%20but%20feel%20this%20problem%20for%20themselves.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDecision%20influenced%20by%20%E2%80%98timeless%E2%80%99%20theme%20of%20book%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECanadian%20writer%20Esi%20Edugyan%2C%20who%20chaired%20the%20judging%20panel%2C%20said%20the%20book%20is%20%E2%80%9Ca%20triumph%20of%20emotional%20storytelling%2C%20bracing%20and%20brave%E2%80%9D%20in%20which%20Lynch%20%E2%80%9Cpulls%20off%20feats%20of%20language%20that%20are%20stunning%20to%20witness.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELynch%E2%80%99s%20win%20comes%20days%20after%20far-right%20violence%20erupted%20in%20Ireland%E2%80%99s%20capital%2C%20Dublin%2C%20following%20a%20stabbing%20attack%20outside%20a%20primary%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEdugyan%20said%20recent%20events%20had%20come%20up%20during%20their%20discussions%20to%20choose%20a%20winner%2C%20but%20it%20was%20not%20the%20reason%20the%20book%20won.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELynch%E2%80%99s%20book%20%E2%80%9Ccaptures%20the%20social%20and%20political%20anxieties%20of%20our%20current%20moment%E2%80%9D%20but%20also%20deals%20with%20%E2%80%9Ctimeless%E2%80%9D%20themes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEdugyan%20said%20the%20choice%20of%20winner%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20unanimous%2C%20but%20the%20meeting%2C%20which%20lasted%20six%20hours%2C%20was%20%E2%80%9Ccollegial.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELynch%20received%20his%20trophy%20from%20last%20year%E2%80%99s%20winner%2C%20Sri%20Lankan%20author%20Shehan%20Karunatilaka%2C%20who%20won%20for%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Seven%20Moons%20of%20Maali%20Almeida%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20novel%20about%20the%20trauma%20of%20the%20civil%20war%20in%20his%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20report%20first%20appeared%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Firish-author-paul-lynch-wins-booker-prize-for-prophet-song%2Fa-67558992%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701056422000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27090716%2FUntitled-design-6-2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Firish-writer-paul-lynch-wins-booker-prize-for-prophet-song%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Lynch's%20novel%20depicts%20an%20Ireland%20descending%20into%20totalitarianism%20in%20the%20near%20future.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A18%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Firish-writer-paul-lynch-wins-booker-prize-for-prophet-song%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22When%20the%20Ceasefire%20Ends%2C%20Biden%20Shouldn't%20Allow%20Israel%20to%20Continue%20Its%20Futile%20War%20of%20Reprisal%20in%20Gaza%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27090342%2Fimage1170x530cropped-6.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20war%20in%20Gaza%20reaching%20the%2050-day%20mark%2C%20239%20hostages%20are%20still%20being%20held%20by%20Hamas%20and%20the%20Islamic%20Jihad%2C%20Israeli%20soldiers%20are%20inside%20Gaza%20City%2C%20and%20as%20a%20result%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20bombing%20campaign%20countless%20buildings%20have%20been%20destroyed%20in%20the%20Northen%20part%20of%20the%20Strip%20and%20an%20unbearable%20number%20of%20civilians%20including%20children%20have%20been%20killed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20the%20ICC%20chief%20prosecutor%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icc-cpi.int%2Fnews%2Fstatement-icc-prosecutor-karim-khan-kc-cairo-situation-state-palestine-and-israel%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Estated%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20during%20his%20visit%20to%20Cairo%2C%20Israel%20needs%20to%20demonstrate%20that%20any%20attack%20that%20impacted%20innocent%20civilians%20or%20protected%20objects%20was%20conducted%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20international%20law%20and%20specifically%20the%20principles%20of%20distinction%2C%20precaution%20and%20of%20proportionality.%20Even%20if%20Israel%20succeeds%20in%20doing%20this%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Esomething%20that%20seems%20very%20challenging%20in%20view%20of%20the%20extent%20of%20the%20destruction%20it%20caused%20in%20Gaza%2C%20the%20question%20arises%3A%20what%20is%20the%20endgame%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3ETo%20really%20overthrow%20the%20Hamas%20regime%2C%20as%20the%20Biden%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.haaretz.co.il%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2F2023-11-04%2Fty-article%2F.premium%2F0000018b-993e-db71-a7df-fdffa3220000%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eadministration%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20Netanyahu%E2%80%99s%20government%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ynet.co.il%2Fnews%2Farticle%2Fryx6v11sm6%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edeclared%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20or%20just%20take%20reprisal%20on%20Hamas%20for%20the%20atrocities%20and%20crimes%20it%20committed%20since%20October%207.%20This%20question%20is%20particularly%20important%20now%20since%20there%20is%20a%20question%20of%20what%20will%20happen%20after%20the%20short%20cease%20fire%20ends.%20The%20war%20may%20drag%20on%20for%20a%20long%20time%20while%20the%20number%20of%20Palestinian%20and%20Israeli%20civilians%20who%20will%20be%20harmed%20will%20only%20increase.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20clear%20that%20the%20only%20suitable%20replacement%20to%20the%20Hamas%20regime%20in%20Gaza%20is%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%20(PA).%20Theoretically%2C%20this%20should%20not%20be%20complicated%2C%20since%20although%20Hamas%20in%20its%20military%20coup%20in%202007%20murdered%20some%20of%20the%20PA%E2%80%99s%20officials%2C%20it%20kept%20a%20large%20part%20of%20its%20bureaucrats%20in%20their%20positions.%20But%2C%20politically%20and%20rightfully%2C%20the%20PA%20will%20not%20be%20able%20to%20agree%20to%20such%20a%20thing%20while%20Israel%20continues%20its%20accelerated%20ethnic%20cleansing%20and%20apartheid%20in%20the%20West%20Bank.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EIn%20their%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.haaretz.co.il%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2F2023-11-05%2Fty-article%2F.premium%2F0000018b-9f50-dbad-abfb-dfdc253f0000%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emeeting%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20November%205%2C%20Palestinian%20President%20Mahmoud%20Abbas%20told%20the%20US%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Antony%20Blinken%20that%20the%20PA%20is%20ready%20to%20accept%20full%20responsibility%20for%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20only%20as%20part%20of%20a%20comprehensive%20political%20solution.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20why%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20seems%20to%20be%20bluffing.%20In%20order%20to%20topple%20the%20Hamas%20regime%2C%20he%20will%20have%20to%20topple%20his%20own%20regime.%20Netanyahu%20only%20cares%20about%20his%20own%20political%20survival%20and%20for%20achieving%20that%20goal%20he%20is%20completely%20dependent%20on%20his%20coalition%20with%20the%20far-right%20parties%20which%20sees%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%20and%20any%20political%20agreement%20with%20it%20as%20a%20bigger%20threat%20than%20Hamas.%20For%20example%2C%20on%20August%2031%2C%202021%2C%20the%20far-right%20and%20supporter%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.middleeasteye.net%2Fopinion%2Fisrael-us-bezalel-smotrich-evidence-genocide-support%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Egenocide%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20Minister%20Bezalel%20Smotritz%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkol-barama.co.il%2Fitem%2F%2525D7%252594%2525D7%252590%2525D7%252596%2525D7%252599%2525D7%2525A0%2525D7%252595-%2525D7%252594%2525D7%252590%2525D7%25259D-%2525D7%2525A1%2525D7%25259E%2525D7%252595%2525D7%252598%2525D7%2525A8%2525D7%252599%2525D7%2525A5-%2525D7%25259E%2525D7%252590%2525D7%2525A9%2525D7%252599%2525D7%25259D-%2525D7%252590%2525D7%2525AA-%2525D7%252591%2525D7%2525A0%2525D7%252598-%2525D7%252591%2525D7%25259E%2525D7%252595%2525D7%2525AA%2525D7%252595%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eexplained%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20an%20interview%20(as%20an%20Member%20of%20Knesset)%20%E2%80%9CIn%20some%20respects%2C%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%20is%20more%20dangerous%20to%20Israel%20than%20Hamas.%20The%20Palestinian%20Authority%20is%20a%20strategic%20threat.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20Hamas%20is%20a%20tactical%20threat%20that%20can%20be%20managed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EThis%20month%2C%20on%20November%203%2C%20Minister%20Smotritz%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.inn.co.il%2Fnews%2F618914%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esaid%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Palestinian%20Authority%20is%20not%20the%20solution%20%E2%80%93%20it%20is%20part%20of%20the%20problem.%20We%20do%20not%20repeat%20mistakes%20and%20concepts%20that%20blew%20up%20in%20our%20faces.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlthough%20Netanyahu%20could%20have%20formed%20an%20alternative%20emergency%20coalition%2C%20even%20temporarily%2C%20only%20the%20far-right%20parties%20are%20willing%20to%20abolish%20the%20independence%20of%20the%20judiciary%20that%20Netanyahu%20needs%20in%20order%20to%20cancel%20or%20stop%20his%20criminal%20trial%20or%20render%20it%20meaningless.%20The%20far-right%20parties%20will%20also%20help%20Netanyahu%20establish%20a%20toothless%20commission%20of%20inquiry%20into%20responsibility%20for%20the%20October%207%20disaster.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EWe%20recently%20saw%20an%20example%20of%20Netanyahu%E2%80%99s%20deep%20attachment%20to%20the%20far-right%20when%20he%20chose%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.haaretz.com%2Fisrael-news%2F2023-11-05%2Fty-article%2Fnetanyahu-criticizes-minister-who-suggested-option-of-dropping-nuclear-bomb-on-gaza%2F0000018b-9e7b-db71-a7df-ffffe4510000%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enot%20to%20fire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20far-right%20Minister%20Amichai%20Eliyahu%20despite%20the%20huge%20international%20damage%20he%20caused%20to%20Israel%20when%20he%20said%20that%20dropping%20a%20nuclear%20weapon%20on%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20is%20%E2%80%9Can%20option.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20not%20difficult%20to%20imagine%20that%20in%20a%20few%20weeks%20from%20now%2C%20after%20many%20more%20Gazan%20civilians%20will%20be%20killed%20and%20most%20of%20the%20hostages%20from%20Israel%20will%20still%20not%20be%20released%2C%20Netanyahu%20will%20have%20a%20celebratory%20press%20conference%20where%20he%20will%20announce%20that%20Israel%20has%20exacted%20a%20heavy%20price%20on%20Hamas%2C%20killed%20thousands%20of%20terrorists%20and%20destroyed%20its%20military%20infrastructure%2C%20but%20in%20practice%20will%20allow%20Hamas%20rule%20to%20continue.%20In%20order%20to%20satisfy%20many%20in%20the%20Israeli%20public%20who%20trusted%20the%20declarations%20of%20his%20government%2C%20Netanyahu%20will%20probably%20claim%20that%20he%20wanted%20to%20overthrow%20the%20Hamas%20regime%20but%20the%20international%20community%20stopped%20him.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20US%20has%20known%20for%20long%20that%20Israel%20has%20a%20strategy%20of%20reprisal.%20According%20to%20a%20US%20Defense%20Intelligence%20Agency%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cia.gov%2Freadingroom%2Fdocs%2FCIA-RDP92T00277R000600150004-1.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eappraisal%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20with%20the%20title%20%E2%80%9CIsrael%3A%20experience%20in%20combating%20terror%E2%80%9D%2C%20that%20was%20made%20on%20June%2011%2C%201984%2C%20and%20declassified%20in%202016%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20commitment%20to%20a%20reprisal%20policy%20is%20deeply%20ingrained%20in%20the%20Israeli%20military%20establishment.%20Although%20Israeli%20military%20intelligence%20officials%20have%20consistently%20warned%20that%20such%20actions%20have%20had%20little%20deterrent%20effect%20on%20terrorists%2C%20the%20leadership%20has%20shown%20a%20willingness%20to%20take%20action%20if%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20security%20interests%20are%20at%20stake%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20document%20explains%20how%20from%20the%201950s%20until%20the%201980s%2C%20Israel%20%E2%80%9Cmoved%20from%20a%20policy%20of%20simple%20eye%20for%20an%20eye%20operation%20to%20a%20fully%20developed%20doctrine%20of%20retaliation.%20This%20held%20that%20terrorism%20could%20be%20countered%20by%20placing%20an%20unacceptably%20high%20price%20(to%20the%20Arabs)%20on%20such%20operations%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlso%20mentioned%20are%20the%20difficulties%20that%20Israel%20faces%20today%20in%20Gaza%2C%20%E2%80%9CNo%20matter%20how%20expertly%20conducted%20from%20a%20military%20perspective%2C%20IDF%20operations%20against%20terrorists%20operating%20from%20bases%20in%20civilian%20areas%20damaged%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20prestige%2C%20the%20image%20of%20its%20military%2C%20and%20its%20relations%20with%20friendly%20states.%20Another%20cost%20%E2%80%9Cis%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20confrontational%20approach%20for%20dealing%20with%20terrorism%20contributed%20to%20its%20perpetuation.%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20large-scale%20actions%20satisfied%20the%20Palestinian%20goal%20of%20eliciting%20a%20strong%20Israeli%20response%2C%20bringing%20attention%2C%20and%20sometimes%20sympathy%2C%20to%20the%20terrorist%20cause.%20Furthermore%2C%20the%20Israeli%20approach%20does%20not%20appear%20to%20have%20hampered%20recruitment%20of%20Palestinians%20willing%20to%20die%20for%20their%20cause.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20the%20US%20Defense%20Intelligence%20Agency%20appraisal%20concludes%2C%20%E2%80%9Capproach%20to%20terrorism%20that%20relies%20primarily%20on%20force%20creates%20a%20dynamic%20of%20stimulus%20and%20response%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20clear%20end%20to%20the%20problem%E2%80%9D.%20The%20only%20solution%20to%20the%20problem%20of%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20as%20well%20as%20to%20the%20entire%20Israeli-Palestinian%20conflict%2C%20is%20diplomatic%20and%20not%20military.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EPresident%20Biden%20should%20not%20allow%20Israel%20to%20continue%20to%20wage%20a%20war%20of%20futile%20reprisal%2C%20which%20will%20solve%20nothing%20and%20only%20cause%20more%20human%20suffering.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EEitay%20Mack%20is%20an%20Israeli%20human%20rights%20lawyer%20and%20activist.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701056102000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27090342%2Fimage1170x530cropped-6.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fgaza-biden-ceasefire-pause%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20only%20solution%20to%20the%20problem%20of%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20as%20well%20as%20to%20the%20entire%20Israeli-Palestinian%20conflict%2C%20is%20diplomatic%20and%20not%20military.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fgaza-biden-ceasefire-pause%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Stock%20market%20holiday%3A%20BSE%2C%20NSE%20closed%20today%20due%20to%20Guru%20Nanak%20Jayanti%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701055924000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-09%2F25%2Ffull%2F1695612851-2693.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fstock-market-holidays-nse-bse-closed-on-november-27-for-guru-nanak-jayanti-123112700101_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Stock%20market%20holiday%20today%3A%20Including%20November%2027%2C%20the%20Indian%20stock%20market%20has%20remained%20closed%20for%2013%20weekdays%20so%20far%20in%202023%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fstock-market-holidays-nse-bse-closed-on-november-27-for-guru-nanak-jayanti-123112700101_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fstock-market-holidays-nse-bse-closed-on-november-27-for-guru-nanak-jayanti-123112700101_1.